Details: A sampling of what you will learn: Tips & tricks to minimize your impacts when you’re in the great outdoors. The best methods to interact with wildlife responsibly. Age-appropriate interactive games to learn the Leave No Trace principles. Develop a sense of environmental stewardship in your children.  Practicing Leave No Trace when camping, biking, fishing, playing in your local park and more. Quick tips to use and share Leave No Trace at home, at work and in your community.
Additional Information: Address: 2389 Stratford Drive Austin, Tx 78746; Phone: (512) 974-3888

Details: Park rangers are partnering with Austin Nature & Science Center to bring nature to every child, everywhere. Join us to explore and play outside with a collection of natural objects like bamboo poles, sticks, and "tree cookies".

Staff: Come and join us on Dec.9th 2016 at the Zilker Caretaker's Cottage from 2-4pm. Park Rangers will be leading a Slacklining program and explain the process of setting up a slackline. Which will include picking out the correct tree, making sure it is protected properly, laying out the line, tightening it up, and the proper technique of walking on the slackline. This program is great for all ages. We hope to see you there.
